[00:00.00][instruction]Welcome to the LRX format template
[00:03.50][instruction]This file demonstrates all available features
[00:07.00][instruction]---
[00:08.50][instruction]Section One: Metadata tags at the top
[00:12.00][instruction]Include artist, title, album, and length
[00:15.50][instruction]Add musical key, creator name, and offset
[00:19.00][instruction]Set global colors with color and background_color tags
[00:23.00][instruction]---
[00:24.50][instruction]Section Two: Track definitions
[00:27.50][instruction]Each track needs a unique ID using dot notation
[00:31.00][instruction]Define name, source file path, and volume
[00:34.50][instruction]Paths are relative to this LRX file location
[00:38.00][instruction]Volume ranges from zero point zero to one point zero
[00:42.00][instruction]---
[00:43.50][instruction]Section Three: Part definitions
[00:46.50][instruction]Parts represent different vocal roles or sections
[00:50.00][instruction]Each part has a unique ID, name, and color
[00:53.50][instruction]Colors use hex format: hashtag R R G G B B
[00:57.50][instruction]---
[00:59.00][instruction]Section Four: Timed lyrics
[01:02.00][instruction]Now let's see examples with actual lyrics
[01:05.50][instruction]---
[01:07.00]This line has no part tag and uses global color
[01:11.00]Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet
[01:14.50]Consectetur adipiscing elit
[01:18.00][lead]This line has the lead part tag
[01:21.50][lead]Sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt
[01:25.00][lead]Ut labore et dolore magna aliqua
[01:29.00][harmony]This line uses the harmony part
[01:32.50][harmony]Ut enim ad minim veniam
[01:36.00][harmony]Quis nostrud exercitation ullamco
[01:40.00][both]This is the both parts tag
[01:43.50][both]Laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo
[01:47.00][instruction]---
[01:48.50][instruction]You can have multiple timestamps for the same line
[01:52.00][lead]Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit
[01:52.00][harmony]Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit
[01:56.00][instruction]Both parts sang that line simultaneously
[01:59.50][instruction]---
[02:01.00][instruction]Special characters and formatting
[02:04.50]♪ Musical note symbols work fine ♪
[02:08.00][lead]Voluptate velit esse cillum dolore
[02:11.50][harmony](Backing vocals in parentheses)
[02:15.00][both]Eu fugiat nulla pariatur
[02:18.50][instruction]---
[02:20.00][instruction]Section Five: Color hierarchy explained
[02:23.50][instruction]Part colors override global colors
[02:27.00][instruction]Lines without part tags use global color
[02:30.50][instruction]If no global color, app defaults are used
[02:34.00][instruction]---
[02:35.50][instruction]Section Six: Timing and offsets
[02:39.00][instruction]Times use minutes, seconds, centiseconds format
[02:42.50][instruction]For example: zero zero colon twelve point fifty
[02:46.00][instruction]Global offset shifts all timestamps uniformly
[02:49.50][instruction]Useful for adjusting sync without editing each line
[02:53.50][instruction]---
[02:55.00][instruction]Section Seven: Track usage examples
[02:58.50][instruction]You can define as many tracks as needed
[03:02.00][instruction]Instrumental, vocals, harmonies, or sound effects
[03:05.50][instruction]Each track can be toggled on or off independently
[03:09.00][instruction]Perfect for karaoke or practice sessions
[03:13.00][instruction]---
[03:14.50][instruction]Section Eight: Best practices
[03:18.00][instruction]Keep track IDs simple: instrumental, vocals, harmony
[03:21.50][instruction]Use descriptive part names: lead, chorus, bridge
[03:25.00][instruction]Choose contrasting colors for easy reading
[03:28.50][instruction]Place audio files in the same folder as this file
[03:32.50][instruction]---
[03:34.00][instruction]To use this template:
[03:37.00][instruction]Replace metadata with your song information
[03:40.50][instruction]Update track sources to your actual audio files
[03:44.00][instruction]Adjust part names and colors as needed
[03:47.50][instruction]Replace these lyrics with your actual song lyrics
[03:51.00][instruction]Time each line to match your audio
[03:54.50][instruction]---
[03:56.00][instruction]Thank you for using the LRX format template
[03:59.50][instruction]Happy syncing!
